Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nb5 d6 6. c4 Nf6 7. N5c3 Be7 8. Be2 {The most popular move, aiming
for rapid development and maintaining control over the f1-a6 diagonal.} O-O
9. O-O b6 {As mentioned before, Black does not need to hurry with ...a7-a6.}
10. Bf4 {Trying to put some pressure on Black's centre.} ({After} 10. Be3 Bb7 {
, Black will soon break with ...d6-d5, one of the main ideas in the Hedgehog.}
11. f4 (11. Nd2 d5 12. cxd5 exd5 13. exd5 Nb4 14. Bf3 Nbxd5 15. Nxd5 Bxd5 16.
