Trying to stay flexible.} (11. Nd2 Rc8 12. Rc1 Ne5 13. a3 Nfd7 $5 $146 (13...
Qd7 $5 14. b4 Rfd8 15. Re1 h6 16. Qb3 Bf8 17. Red1 g5 18. Be3 Qe7 19. Nb5 Bc6
$11 {[%cal Gf8g7]}) 14. b4 g5 {The same plan as in the main line.} 15. Be3 h6
16. Qb3 Kh7 $132) 11... Rc8 12. Bf1 Ne5 13. Nd2 Nfd7 14. Bg3 g5 {Since White's
control in the centre is weak and his dark-squared bishop has consumed some
time, this plan is very adequate. Black can regroup on dark squares at leisure.
Here are a few examples.} 15. Rc1 a6 (15... Qc7 16. b4 Qb8 17. a3 Rfd8 18. Qh5
Ng6 19. h3 Kg7 20. Qd1 Nde5 21. Nb5 Bf6 22. Nb3 h5 23. f3 (23. Qxh5 $2 g4 {
[%cal Gd8h8]}) 23... Bc6 24. N5d4 Ba4 $17 {Lopez Martinez,J (2506)-Fluvia
Poyatos,J (2490) Catalunya-ch 2012 (2.1) 0-1}) 16. f3 (16. b4 Kh8 17. a3 Rg8
18. Na4 Ng6 19. Nb3 Nf4 20. Nd4 Qf8 21. Nb3 Qd8 22. Nd4 Ne5 23. Nb3 Bc6 24. b5
Be8 25. Qd4 Rb8 26. Red1 {Hacker,J (2345)-Milov,L (2481) Bayern-chI Bank
Hofmann 22nd 2018 (7) 1/2-1/2} h5 27. h3 Rg7 $132) 16... Kh8 17. Bf2 Rg8 18. h3
Rg7 19. b4 h5 20. a3 Qg8 21. Re3 Qh7 22. Ne2 Rcg8 23. Rcc3 Rg6 (23... Qh6 24.
Nb3 Rh7 $17) 24. f4 gxf4 25. Nxf4 {Kavalek,L (2545)-Liberzon,V (2550) IBM-17
Grootmeestergroep A 1977 (12) 0-1} Rg5 $15 *

