{[%evp 0,34,23,20,49,33,39,38,38,38,45,31,43,28,28,28,65,60,3,4,39,51,48,7,29,
17,46,-107,-112,-43,-36,-33,42,15,39,-25,-92]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4.
Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nb5 d6 6. Bf4 {This used to be one of Fischer's favourite systems.
White is heading for a Sveshnikov structure, even though he will practically
be a tempo down. During Fischer's best years, Sveshnikov had not analyzed his
system yet and theory was rather skeptical about it. During my childhood, the
Sveshnikov system was named after the Czech-Argentinian master Jiri (Jorge)
Pelikan. In any case, the fact that White was a tempo down did not put off
Fischer, since the Pelikan system was considered dubious.} e5 7. Bg5 $2 {
An incorrect sacrifice, hoping to convince Black to transpose to a genuine
Pelikan/Sveshnikov with 7...Nf6.} (7. Bg3 {is inoffensive.} Nf6 8. N5c3 {
Jiang,Q (1370)-Danilov,A (1693) Gatineau Benevoles 2012 (2) 0-1} (8. N1c3 a6 9.
Na3 b5 $15) 8... Qb6 9. Qc1 Be7 10. Nd2 Be6 $15) (7. Be3 {is examined in Lines
16 and 17.}) 7... Qxg5 $1 {Black should not fear any ghosts.} ({If he does, he
can also play} 7... Be7 {, which is good for equality only.} 8. Bxe7 Kxe7 9.
N1c3 Nf6 10. Nd5+ Nxd5 11. exd5 a6 12. Nc3 Nd4 13. Bd3 {Black is doing well
from a strategic point of view but needs to care about his slightly exposed
knight and king.} Re8 (13... Bd7 14. O-O Qb6 15. Qd2 Rhc8 {Aiguasenosa,S-Reyes,
A UECC email 1999 (7) 0-1} 16. Qg5+ Kf8 17. Bxh7 $16) 14. O-O Kf8 15. Ne4 Kg8
16. Ng3 (16. f4 f5 $11) 16... Qg5 17. a4 {[%cal Ga1a3,Ga4a5]} Nf5 18. Ne4 Qd8
19. Ra3 (19. a5 Ne7 20. Ng5 f5 21. Qh5 h6 22. Qf7+ Kh8 23. Ra3 Rf8 24. Be2 f4
25. Qh5 Bf5 26. Nf7+ Rxf7 27. Qxf7 Bg6 28. Qe6 Bf5 $11) 19... b6 20. Re1 Rf8
$11) (7... Nf6 8. N1c3 {transposes to the Sveshnikov.}) 8. Nc7+ Kd8 9. Nxa8 Nf6
{The knight on a8 canot return into play easily and Black is better developed.}
10. Nc3 (10. Nd2 Bg4 11. f3 Be6 12. a4 Be7 13. a5 Kd7 14. a6 {Didenko, S (2130)
-Andreev,V (1908) Geller Memorial op-A 3rd 2007 (8) 0-1} Rxa8 15. axb7 Rb8 $19)
10... Nd4 11. Qd3 (11. h4 Qg4 12. Qd3 Be6 13. g3 Qf3 14. Qxf3 Nxf3+ 15. Ke2
Nd4+ 16. Kd3 Ng4 17. Nd1 f5 $19 18. Bg2 fxe4+ 19. Bxe4 d5 20. Bg2 Bd6 21. c3
Nc6 {Gyger,T (2396)-Stull,N (2584) olm18 sf04 email 2009 [2] 0-1}) 11... d5 $1
(11... Be6 12. Nd5 $17) 12. Rd1 (12. Nxd5 Nxd5 13. exd5 Bf5 14. Qc4 Bd6 15. Bd3
Ke7 16. Bxf5 Qxf5 17. O-O Rxa8 $19 {Mueller Toepler,M (1943)-Salminen,J (1960)
FIN-GER email 2015 0-1}) 12... Bd7 13. Rd2 Bd6 14. Qe3 Qg6 15. f4 Qh6 16. Nxd5
Nxd5 17. exd5 Re8 $19 *

