a7-a6, but also hurries to reach this structure before White has defined his
queen knight's intentions.}) 5. Nxc6 (5. Nc3 a6 6. Nxc6 bxc6 {is very
fashionable nowadays. True, the knight blocks the path of the c-pawn, but
Black has wasted a tempo on ...a7-a6 anyway.}) 5... bxc6 {Black did not waste
any tempo in this line and the square on b6 is not weak. Moreover, in some
cases he can exchange his potentially passive bishop for White's active one
with ...Ba6.} 6. Bd3 (6. c4 Nf6 {transposes to Line XX}) 6... Nf6 7. O-O d5 {
This is the typical structure I had been talking about earlier.} 8. Nd2 (8. e5
