{[%evp 0,40,17,13,37,37,37,28,28,22,35,29,65,43,43,43,50,29,52,43,74,70,46,46,
59,76,87,46,56,21,2,1,16,25,101,46,194,194,189,-3,-3,-3,-3]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3
Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 e6 5. Nc3 d6 6. g4 Nge7 7. Be3 a6 8. f4 b5 9. Bg2 {
With three kingside pawns on the fourth rank, implying superior structural
mobility, this way of developing the bishop is more consistent than in some
lines above.} (9. Nxc6 Nxc6 {We know a bit about this exchange already.} 10.
Bg2 {And about this move, too.} Bb7 11. Qd2 (11. g5 {Bodnaruk,A (2431)
-Charochkina,D (2310) RUS-ch (Women) 61st 2011 (2) 0-1} Rc8 12. Qd2 Na5 13. b3
d5 14. Ne2 Ba3 $11) 11... Qh4+ {Why not?} 12. Bf2 Qxg4 13. Rg1 {Bok, B (2453)
-Grabarczyk, B (2448) Bundesliga 1011 2010 (9.5) 1-0 White has certain
compensation for the pawn, but Black can react energetically.} g5 {As we will
