13. Bg2 Be7 (13... b4 14. Ne2 $16) 14. O-O O-O 15. f5 (15. g5 Bd8 16. f5 b4 17.
Ne2 exf5 18. exf5 Bxg2 19. Qxg2 Nb6 $132 {Vitiugov, N (2718)-Babula, V (2548)
EU-Cup 32nd Novi Sad 2016 (3.3) 1/2-1/2}) 15... Qd8 (15... Qc7 16. g5) 16. e5
Bxg2 17. Qxg2 d5 {Jordan,J (2197)-Daelemans,H (1587) IECG WC Cand email 2008
1-0} 18. Kh1 $16) 10. f5 $146 {Never tried in practice, this seems to be the
most consistent answer. White maintains his structure compact and attacks g5.}
(10. fxg5 Ne5 11. Bd3 (11. Qe2 {Geller,J (2539)-Shcherbakov,R (2516) Izhevsk
op-A 2010 (9) 1-0} b4 12. Na4 Rb8 13. O-O-O Qc7 14. h4 Bg7 15. h5 O-O $15)
11... N7g6 (11... Bg7 12. h4 O-O $15) 12. Be2 Nh4 13. Rg1 {Feletar,D (2330)
-Rogic, D (2455) Zagreb op 1997 (8) 1/2-1/2} b4 14. Na4 Bb7 15. Nb6 Rb8 $17)
10... Ne5 11. Qe2 {The most desirable developing move, preparing the king's
evacuation.} (11. Bxg5 $2 {offers Black too much play.} b4 12. Bf6 (12. Ne2
Nf3+) (12. Nb1 Rg8 13. h4 h6 14. Bxe7 Bxe7 $19) (12. Na4 Rg8 13. h4 Bd7 14.
Qxd6 Nf3+ 15. Kf2 Nxg5 16. hxg5 Bxa4 $19) 12... bxc3 $1 (12... Rg8 13. Bxe5
