$13) (20. gxf7+ Rxf7 21. Rhg1 Kh8 $13) 20... fxg6 (20... Qc6 21. b3 (21. gxf7+
Rxf7 22. Rg1 Rd7 $15 {reveals one more merit of the rook lift.}) 21... Ba6 22.
Bxa6 Qxa6 23. f4 c4 $132) 21. hxg6 Qc6 22. Qe2 Ba6 23. Bxa6 Rxa6 24. f4 c4 25.
b3 c3 $13 {With the knight isolated on a4 and his king in potential danger
along the back rank, White cannot hope for an advantage.} *

