Rfb8 18. Na4 Qxe3+ 19. Kxe3 a5 20. Nc5 Kf8 21. Nxe6+ fxe6 22. c3 Ke7 23. Rfb1
Nd7 24. a4 Ra7 $11) 17. Na4 Nd7 18. Qf2 (18. Ba6 $5) 18... Rfd8 19. Rfd1 a5 20.
Nc5 Nxc5 21. Qxc5 Qd6 22. Qxd6 Rxd6 23. Kf2 Kf8 24. Ke3 Ke7 25. Rdb1 Bd7 26.
Be2 f5 27. exf5 Bxf5 28. b5 Bxc2 29. Rb2 $11 {Steinberg,M-Novopashin,A
UKR-ch37 Kiev 1968 (6) 1/2-1/2}) 11... O-O (11... Bg4 $5 12. Qg3 Qb8 13. Bb3
Bh5 $13) 12. h3 {White needs to spend a tempo on taking g4 under control.} (12.
O-O {allows} Ng4 13. Rad1 (13. Bxf7+ $2 Kh8 14. Qe2 Nxe3 15. Qxe3 Qd4 16. Qxd4
exd4 17. Na4 Ba6 18. Rf3 Be2 19. Rf2 Bb5 20. Bb3 Rxf2 21. Kxf2 Rf8+ 22. Kg1 c5
23. c4 Bc6 $17) 13... Nxe3 $1 14. Bxf7+ Kh8 15. Qxe3 (15. Rxd8 Bxd8 16. Re1 Ng4
17. Na4 Nh6 $17) 15... Qb6 16. Qxb6 axb6 {Rightly given by Kasparov and
Nikitin as offering Black adequate compensation for the pawn.} 17. Bc4 Bg4 18.
Rxf8+ Rxf8 19. Rf1 Bc5+ 20. Kh1 Rxf1+ 21. Bxf1 Bd4 22. h3 Bxc3 23. hxg4 {
