$11) 14... Qc7 15. Nd4 (15. Bf4 Ne5 $11) 15... Nxd4 16. Bxd4 Nd7 17. Bd3 a6 {
Black has finally found the time to catch up with the Najdorf setup.} 18.
Nd5 Bxd5 19. exd5 Rce8 $1 (19... Bf6 $2 20. Bxf6 Nxf6 21. Rxf6 gxf6 22. Qh6 f5
23. Bxf5 f6 24. Be6+ Kh8 25. Bxc8 Qxc8 26. Re1 $18) 20. Rde1 (20. Kh1 {is most
