Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 d6 6. Bc4 Nf6 7. Be3 {This usually is a declaration of White's
intentions to castle long but also maintains the possibility to switch to the
Fischer Sozin Attack.} Bd7 {This move order is mainly aimed at allowing to
meet the long castle with the quickest possible counterplay. Fortunately, it
works well if White castles short, too.} ({There is too much theory
accumulated in the old main lines} 7... Be7 8. Qe2 O-O 9. O-O-O a6 10. Bb3 Qc7
11. Rhg1 (11. g4 Nxd4 12. Rxd4 b5 13. g5 Nd7 14. Rg1) 11... b5 12. g4) 8. Qe2 {
