leaves the rook on a8 hanging.}) 28. Bxf7+ $1 Kh8 29. Qe7 {and the rook on f8
is hanging.} Rg8 30. Rad1 $1 $11) 27. Kh1 (27. Kh2 {allows} Rad8 28. Bxf7+ Kh8
{because the rook will reach d2 with check.}) 27... Qe4+ $1 28. Kg1 Rfd8 $1 29.
Bxf7+ Kh8 {The white queen cannot put an eye on the rook on a8.} 30. Qc5 Qg4+
31. Kh2 Qh4+ (31... Rd2+ 32. Rf2) 32. Kg2 Rac8 $1 33. Qf2 Qg5+ 34. Kh1 Rd2 $19)
24... Nf2+ $11 *

