3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 d6 6. g3 Nf6 7. Bg2 Bd7 8. O-O Be7 9. Be3 {
The most natural move.} O-O 10. h3 {Played at this stage, this discards
White's intentions to attack with g3-g4.} (10. g4 $2 {loses a pawn to} Nxd4 11.
Bxd4 e5 $17) (10. Qe2 {is examined in Lines 60 and 61.}) 10... a6 11. a4 {
Trying to keep Black's counterplay under control.} (11. g4 {is the main
alternative.} Nxd4 12. Qxd4 (12. Bxd4 Bc6 13. g5 Nd7 14. h4 (14. f4 {Ajay
Krishna, S (2367)-Garrido, D (2205) Titled Tuesday intern op 16th Aug Early
blitz 2022 (10) 1-0} e5 $1 15. Be3 exf4 16. Bxf4 Bxg5 17. Bxd6 Re8 $17) 14...
