14. Bc1 Rac8 15. f4 h6 (15... b5 16. axb6 Qxb6+ 17. Kh1 Bb5 18. Nxb5 axb5 $11
19. f5 exf5 20. exf5 Rfe8 21. c3 d5 $17 {Pacl,V (2320)-Plachetka,J (2440)
CSR-ch52 International 1984 (1) 0-1}) (15... d5 16. e5 Ne8 {is also good, even
though less appealing optically.}) 16. g4 (16. Kh1 Rfe8 17. g4 Nh7 $17) 16...
d5 17. e5 (17. exd5 Rfe8 18. g5 Nxd5 19. gxh6 Nxc3 20. bxc3 g6 $17) 17... Nh7
$17 {[%cal Gg7g5,Gf7f6] followed by either ...g7-g5 or ...f7-f6.}) 12... Bxc6
13. a5 {The main idea behind the previous move.} Nd7 14. Rfd1 Rac8 15. f4 Rfe8
{The most flexible move.} (15... Bf6 {is also good, but a bit more demanding.}
16. Qd2 Bxc3 17. Qxc3 f5 $5 $146 {This should be Black's main plan after
exchanging on c3.} (17... Rfe8 18. Qb4 {Quesada Perez,Y (2636)-Saric,I (2668)
ESP-chT Div Honor 2016 (4.4) 1/2-1/2} f5 19. Qxd6 Qxd6 20. Rxd6 Nf6 21. e5 Bxg2
22. exf6 Bd5 $11) 18. exf5 (18. Qd4 Nf6 19. Qxd6 Qf7 20. exf5 Bxg2 21. fxe6 Qh5
22. Kxg2 Qe2+ 23. Bf2 Rxc2 24. Rf1 Rd2 25. Qc5 (25. Qb6 Nd5 $17) (25. Qa3 Qxe6
26. Rae1 Qd5+ 27. Qf3 Qb5 $44) 25... Qxe6 26. Rae1 Qb3 $44) 18... Bxg2 19. Kxg2
(19. fxe6 Bc6 20. exd7 Qxd7 21. Rd4 Rce8 22. Rf1 Qf5 $44) (19. Qxc7 Rxc7 20.
fxe6 Bf3 21. Rf1 Bg4 22. exd7 Rxc2 23. f5 Rd8 $11) 19... exf5 20. Bd4 Qxc3 21.
Bxc3 Rc6 22. Kf3 h5 23. Rac1 Nc5 24. Bd4 Ne4 25. c3 Kf7 26. Rc2 Re8 $11) 16.
Qd2 Bf8 17. Qf2 g6 18. Ba7 (18. Bd4 e5 19. Be3 exf4 20. Qxf4 {Koffeman,T (2101)
