{[#]} 12... Nd7 (12... d5 $2 13. Rd1 $16 Bd6 $2 14. Rxf6 $1 Qxf6 15. exd5 Qe5
16. Qg3 Qxc3 17. bxc3 Bxg3 18. hxg3 Rfe8 19. dxc6 $18 {Vnukov,D-Bonthuis,S
IECG L2.1999.0.00004 email 1-0}) 13. Rf1 (13. Qg3 {Tomczak,J (2448)-Panas,P 
(2226) Polanica Zdroj op-A 43rd 2007 (1) 1-0} Bg5 $11) 13... Bf6 14. Rd1 Be5 {
The bishop has reached an optimal square. The knight on c3 cannot jump to d5
without leaving b2 undefended. Therefore, now or in the near future, White
needs to exchange it, which favours Black strategically.} *

