{[#]} 12... Bxd5 13. exd5 Ne5 {The similar Najdorf position has by far more
practical material than the current one, but the evaluation is the same: Black
is doing fine. His key piece is the e5-knight and the bishop is also supposed
to play a part on the dark squares. White has more space in the centre and
certain queenside pressure. His main hope is to carry out c4-c5 under
favourable circumstances. Lothar Vogt used to be another specialist of this
line. He was a friend and an analyzing partner of Rainer Knaak for many years.
They both belonged to the Democratic German chess school, based on fundamental
concepts and principal lines.} *

